## 2048 / Sliding Puzzle Grid Logic

Grid manipulation, merging, and scoring for 2048-style games.

### Grid Data
```typescript
const SIZE = 4;
let grid: number[][] = Array.from({ length: SIZE }, () => Array(SIZE).fill(0));

function addRandomTile() {
  const empty: [number, number][] = [];
  for (let r = 0; r < SIZE; r++)
    for (let c = 0; c < SIZE; c++)
      if (grid[r][c] === 0) empty.push([r, c]);
  if (empty.length === 0) return;
  const [r, c] = Phaser.Utils.Array.GetRandom(empty);
  grid[r][c] = Math.random() < 0.9 ? 2 : 4;
}
```

### Slide & Merge (one direction)
```typescript
function slideRow(row: number[]): { result: number[]; score: number } {
  let nums = row.filter(v => v !== 0);
  let score = 0;
  for (let i = 0; i < nums.length - 1; i++) {
    if (nums[i] === nums[i + 1]) {
      nums[i] *= 2; score += nums[i]; nums.splice(i + 1, 1);
    }
  }
  while (nums.length < SIZE) nums.push(0);
  return { result: nums, score };
}
```

### Four Directions via Rotation
```typescript
function move(dir: 'left' | 'right' | 'up' | 'down') {
  let rotated = dir === 'up' || 'down' ? transpose(grid) : grid.map(r => [...r]);
  if (dir === 'right' || dir === 'down') rotated = rotated.map(r => r.reverse());
  let totalScore = 0;
  rotated = rotated.map(row => { const s = slideRow(row); totalScore += s.score; return s.result; });
  if (dir === 'right' || dir === 'down') rotated = rotated.map(r => r.reverse());
  grid = dir === 'up' || dir === 'down' ? transpose(rotated) : rotated;
  score += totalScore;
  addRandomTile();
}
```

### Tips
- Win condition: any tile reaches 2048
- Lose condition: no empty cells AND no adjacent merges possible
- Animate tile movement with tweens for smooth feel
- Color tiles by value using a lookup map

