### Interpolate Remote Players
```typescript
const remotePlayers: Map<string, { sprite: Phaser.GameObjects.Sprite; targetX: number; targetY: number }> = new Map();
function updateWorldState(state: any) {
  state.players.forEach((p: any) => {
    const remote = remotePlayers.get(p.id);
    if (remote) { remote.targetX = p.x; remote.targetY = p.y; }
  });
}
// In update: lerp to target
remotePlayers.forEach(r => {
  r.sprite.x = Phaser.Math.Linear(r.sprite.x, r.targetX, 0.2);
  r.sprite.y = Phaser.Math.Linear(r.sprite.y, r.targetY, 0.2);
});
```

### Tips
- Send inputs, not positions (server-authoritative model prevents cheating)
- Interpolate remote players for smooth movement
- Use delta compression: only send what changed
